# Design System Rules

This document provides comprehensive guidelines for implementing designs from Figma into
code, understanding our token system, and maintaining consistency across the frontend.

## 1. Design System Overview

### Tech Stack

- **UI Framework**: Chakra UI v3 (`@chakra-ui/react` v3.31.0)
- **React Version**: React 19
- **Build Tool**: Vite 8 with Tanstack Router plugin
- **State Management**: Jotai + Tanstack Query
- **Routing**: Tanstack Router
- **Package Manager**: Bun (use `bun` instead of `npm`)

### Project Structure

```text
frontend/
├── components/
│   └── ui/           # Chakra UI component wrappers
├── routes/           # Tanstack Router file-based routes
├── queries/          # Tanstack Query definitions
├── theme/            # Design tokens and theme configuration
│   ├── index.ts      # Main theme system export
│   ├── global-css.ts # Global styles
│   ├── text-styles.ts
│   ├── recipes/      # Component recipes (variants)
│   ├── semantic-tokens/
│   │   ├── colors.ts
│   │   └── shadows.ts
│   └── tokens/
│       ├── colors.ts
│       ├── fonts.ts
│       ├── font-sizes.ts
│       ├── font-weights.ts
│       ├── letter-spacings.ts
│       ├── line-heights.ts
│       └── radii.ts
└── main.tsx          # Application entry point
```

## 2. Token Definitions

### 2.1 Color Tokens

#### Base Colors (in `frontend/theme/tokens/colors.ts`)

| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `black` | `#141414` | True black |
| `white` | `#FFFFFF` | True white |
| `common.black` | `#141414` | Alias for black |
| `common.white` | `#FFFFFF` | Alias for white |

#### Color Palettes

Each palette has shades from 50-950:

| Palette | Primary Shade | Usage |
|---------|---------------|-------|
| `purple` | `#4E49D1` (500) | Primary brand color |
| `gray`/`neutral` | `#71727A` (500) | Neutral tones |
| `green` | `#12BB99` (500) | Success states |
| `red` | `#DB3142` (500) | Error/danger states |
| `yellow` | `#F3DF00` (500) | Warning states |
| `blue`/`lightBlue` | `#50ADC9` (500) | Info states |

**Note**: `gray` and `neutral` point to the same palette. `blue` and `lightBlue` also
point to the same palette.

### 2.2 Semantic Color Tokens (in `frontend/theme/semantic-tokens/colors.ts`)

Semantic tokens provide meaning-based color access with light/dark mode support.

#### Background Tokens (`bg.*`)

```tsx
// Usage examples:
<Box bg="bg" />           // Default background
<Box bg="bg.subtle" />    // Subtle background (neutral.50 / neutral.950)
<Box bg="bg.muted" />     // Muted background (neutral.100 / neutral.900)
<Box bg="bg.emphasized" /> // Emphasized background
<Box bg="bg.panel" />     // Panel background
<Box bg="bg.modal" />     // Modal background
<Box bg="bg.level1" />    // Elevation level 1
<Box bg="bg.level2" />    // Elevation level 2
<Box bg="bg.level3" />    // Elevation level 3
<Box bg="bg.error" />     // Error background (red.50 / red.950)
<Box bg="bg.warning" />   // Warning background
<Box bg="bg.success" />   // Success background
<Box bg="bg.info" />      // Info background
```

#### Foreground Tokens (`fg.*`)

```tsx
<Text color="fg" />         // Default text color
<Text color="fg.muted" />   // Muted text
<Text color="fg.subtle" />  // Subtle text
<Text color="fg.error" />   // Error text
<Text color="fg.warning" /> // Warning text
<Text color="fg.success" /> // Success text
```

#### Text Tokens (`text.*`)

```tsx
<Text color="text.main" />     // Primary text
<Text color="text.light" />    // Secondary text
<Text color="text.lighter" />  // Tertiary text
<Text color="text.inverse" />  // Inverse (for dark backgrounds)
<Text color="text.link" />     // Link color (purple.500 / purple.400)
```

#### Border Tokens (`border.*`)

```tsx
<Box borderColor="border" />           // Default border
<Box borderColor="border.muted" />     // Muted border
<Box borderColor="border.subtle" />    // Subtle border
<Box borderColor="border.emphasized" /> // Emphasized border
<Box borderColor="border.error" />     // Error border
```

#### Primary Color Tokens (`primary.*`)

The primary color palette (purple) has semantic tokens for consistent branding:

```tsx
// Chakra V3 standard tokens
<Box bg="primary.solid" />      // Solid primary (purple.600)
<Text color="primary.fg" />     // Primary foreground
<Box bg="primary.subtle" />     // Subtle primary background
<Box bg="primary.muted" />      // Muted primary background
<Box bg="primary.emphasized" /> // Emphasized primary

// Custom semantic tokens
<Text color="primary.text.main" />    // Primary text color
<Text color="primary.text.light" />   // Light primary text
<Text color="primary.text.lighter" /> // Lighter primary text
<Box bg="primary.bg.main" />          // Primary background
<Box bg="primary.bg.light" />         // Light primary background
<Box bg="primary.bg.lighter" />       // Lighter primary background
<Box bg="primary.bg.contrast" />      // Contrast primary background
```

#### Status Color Tokens

Similar patterns exist for `danger.*`, `warning.*`, `success.*`, and `info.*`:

```tsx
<Text color="danger.text.main" />
<Box bg="danger.bg.main" />
<Text color="success.text.main" />
<Box bg="warning.bg.lighter" />
```

### 2.3 Typography Tokens

#### Font Families (in `frontend/theme/tokens/fonts.ts`)

```tsx
<Text fontFamily="body" />     // Public Sans with fallbacks
<Heading fontFamily="heading" /> // Public Sans with Georgia fallback
<Code fontFamily="mono" />     // SFMono-Regular with fallbacks
```

The project uses **Public Sans** as the primary font, loaded via `@fontsource/public-sans`
with weights: 300, 400, 500, 600, 700.

#### Font Sizes (in `frontend/theme/tokens/font-sizes.ts`)

| Token | Value | Pixels (base 16px) |
|-------|-------|-------------------|
| `2xs` | `0.625rem` | 10px |
| `xs` | `0.75rem` | 12px |
| `sm` | `0.875rem` | 14px |
| `md` | `1rem` | 16px |
| `lg` | `1.125rem` | 18px |
| `xl` | `1.25rem` | 20px |
| `2xl` | `1.5rem` | 24px |
| `3xl` | `1.875rem` | 30px |
| `4xl` | `2.25rem` | 36px |
| `5xl` | `3rem` | 48px |

#### Font Weights (in `frontend/theme/tokens/font-weights.ts`)

| Token | Value |
|-------|-------|
| `light` | 300 |
| `normal` | 400 |
| `medium` | 500 |
| `semibold` | 600 |
| `bold` | 700 |

#### Text Styles (in `frontend/theme/text-styles.ts`)

Pre-defined text style compositions:

```tsx
// Headings
<Text textStyle="display" />  // 4xl, bold, 150% line-height
<Text textStyle="h1" />       // 4xl, medium
<Text textStyle="h2" />       // 3xl, medium
<Text textStyle="h3" />       // xl, medium
<Text textStyle="h4" />       // md, medium, 133% line-height
<Text textStyle="h5" />       // sm, medium
<Text textStyle="h6" />       // xs, medium

// Body text
<Text textStyle="bodyXL" />   // xl, normal
<Text textStyle="body1" />    // md, normal, 150% line-height
<Text textStyle="body2" />    // sm, normal, 133% line-height
<Text textStyle="body3" />    // xs, normal

// Buttons
<Text textStyle="buttonL" />  // md, medium
<Text textStyle="buttonM" />  // sm, medium
<Text textStyle="buttonS" />  // xs, medium

// Special
<Text textStyle="chipXS" />   // 0.5rem, medium
<Text textStyle="inherit" />  // Inherits all typography from parent
```

### 2.4 Spacing and Layout

Chakra UI uses a spacing scale based on 4px increments. Use numeric values:

```tsx
<Box p="4" />     // 16px padding (4 * 4px)
<Box mt="2" />    // 8px margin-top
<Box gap="6" />   // 24px gap
```

### 2.5 Border Radius (in `frontend/theme/tokens/radii.ts`)

| Token | Value |
|-------|-------|
| `none` | 0 |
| `2xs` | 0.0625rem (1px) |
| `xs` | 0.125rem (2px) |
| `sm` | 0.25rem (4px) |
| `base` | 0.375rem (6px) |
| `md` | 0.5rem (8px) |
| `lg` | 1rem (16px) |
| `xl` | 1.5rem (24px) |
| `2xl` | 2.5rem (40px) |
| `full` | 9999px (circular) |

### 2.6 Shadows (in `frontend/theme/semantic-tokens/shadows.ts`)

```tsx
<Box shadow="outline" />     // Focus ring shadow
<Box shadow="level1" />      // Subtle elevation
<Box shadow="level2" />      // Medium elevation
<Box shadow="level3" />      // High elevation
<Box shadow="dropdownBg" />  // Dropdown shadow
<Box shadow="modalBg" />     // Modal shadow
```

